The paper deals with the problem of grounding textual phrases in visual content, which is a task that involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves learning through attention mechanisms, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper deals with datasets and supervision, which are relevant to information retrieval (IR).
